{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, our analysis flagged entities such as \"polycystic ovary syndrome,\" \"non-alcoholic fatty liver disease,\" and \"micro plastics\" alongside more traditional chemical compounds.",
    "This diversity highlights the complex, multifaceted nature of carcinogenesis and the importance of considering a wide range of potential contributing factors.",
    "Many of these nominees are not currently listed in major carcinogen databases, suggesting that they may represent emerging areas of concern or contentious cases requiring further study.",
    "For example, \"ochratoxin A,\" a mycotoxin found in various food products, was identified in our analysis with 162 supporting publications spanning from 2000 to 2022.",
    "Similarly, \"borna disease virus\" emerged as a nominee with 144 supporting publications from 2000 to 2022."
  ]
}